# ArticleCardBySlug

## Purpose
React Router `.tsx` wrapper component that resolves article metadata from the articles registry by `slug` and renders an `ArticleCard`. It handles date formatting, author resolution, and fallback image selection automatically.

## Props

### Required
| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `slug` | `string` | Article slug to look up in the registry |

### Optional
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `ctaText` | `string` | `'Read more'` | Call-to-action button text |
| `className` | `string` | - | Additional CSS classes |
| `descriptionOverride` | `string` | - | Override the article description |
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'compact'` | `'default'` | Card size variant |
| `authorOverride` | `Author` | - | Override the article author |

## Semantic Hints
`card`, `article-card`, `slug-card`, `dynamic-card`, `registry-card`, `auto-card`

## When to Use
Use in React Router route modules when the route already has one or more article slugs and should render cards without manually mapping every article field. Prefer route-level `loader` functions for selecting which slugs to show.

## Behavior
1. Looks up the article by slug in the articles registry
2. Extracts title, description, image, date, and author
3. Formats the date for display
4. Resolves the author from the authors registry when the article stores an author id
5. Provides a fallback image if none is specified
6. Renders `ArticleCard` with resolved data

## Structure
```tsx
<ArticleCardBySlug slug="my-article" />
// renders:
// <ArticleCard {...resolvedProps} />
```

## Styling Guidelines
- Inherits all styling from `ArticleCard`
- Accepts `className` and passes it through
- Use Tailwind utilities at the layout level, e.g. route grids and sections

## Error Handling
- If the slug is not found in the registry:
  - Return `null`
  - Log a development warning to the console

