# ArticleSummaryCard (React Router, `.tsx`)

## Purpose
Key points summary box with distinctive Tailwind styling. Shows a heading, optional intro text, and a bulleted list of items with label and description. Use in React Router article routes for TL;DR sections, highlights, and AI Overview optimization.

## Props

### Required
| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `summary` | `SummaryData` | Summary object with heading, intro, and items |

### Optional
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `className` | `string` | - | Additional CSS classes |
| `variant` | `'indigo' \| 'gray' \| 'brand'` | `'indigo'` | Color variant |

## Types
```ts
interface SummaryData {
    heading?: string;
    intro?: string;
    items: SummaryItem[];
}

interface SummaryItem {
    label: string;
    description: string;
}
```

## Semantic Hints
`summary`, `key-facts`, `tldr`, `highlights`, `overview`, `key-points`, `summary-box`, `takeaways`

## When to Use
Use near the top of React Router article routes to show 3–5 key facts or takeaways. Pass summary as `{ heading, intro, items: [{ label, description }] }`. Prefer route-level `loader` data when the summary is CMS- or content-driven.

## Structure
```tsx
<ArticleSummaryCard>
    <section>
        <h2>Key points</h2>
        <p>Optional intro text</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Label</strong>
                <span>Description</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</ArticleSummaryCard>
```

## Styling Guidelines
- Container: rounded corners, colored background, left border accent
- Heading: bold, slightly larger than body
- Items: semantic list with comfortable spacing
- Label: semibold, inline with description
- Color scheme: `indigo` by default
- `brand` uses default Tailwind `blue-*` utilities unless project theme tokens define brand colors

## Variants
| Variant | Background | Border | Text |
|---------|------------|--------|------|
| `indigo` | `bg-indigo-50` | `border-indigo-500` | `text-indigo-950` |
| `gray` | `bg-gray-50` | `border-gray-400` | `text-gray-950` |
| `brand` | `bg-blue-50` | `border-blue-500` | `text-blue-950` |

## Accessibility
- Use a semantic heading; default is `<h2>`
- Use `<ul>` for the items list
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Labels are rendered with `<strong>` for visual and semantic hierarchy

## Complete React Router Example

### `app/components/article-summary-card.tsx`
