# ArticleCalendarSection (React Router, `.tsx`)

## Purpose
Interactive article archive calendar for a React Router route. Clickable dates filter articles by published day through URL state/search params. Includes month navigation, paginated article links, and date-filter mode.

## Props

### Required
| Prop | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `title` | `string` | Section title |
| `articles` | `Article[]` | All articles for calendar |
| `paginatedArticles` | `Article[]` | Currently visible articles |
| `currentPage` | `number` | Current pagination page |
| `totalPages` | `number` | Total number of pages |
| `pageSize` | `number` | Articles per page |
| `paginationBasePath` | `string` | Base URL for pagination links |

### Optional
| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `string` | `'calendar'` | Section ID for anchor linking |
| `paginationHash` | `string` | - | Hash to append to pagination URLs |
| `selectedDate` | `Date` | - | Currently selected date |
| `onDateSelect` | `(date: Date) => void` | - | Callback when date clicked |

## Types
```ts
type Article = {
    slug: string;
    title: string;
    date: string;
    description?: string;
    image?: string;
};
```

## Semantic Hints
`calendar`, `schedule`, `dates`, `events-calendar`, `date-picker`, `archive`, `timeline`

## When to Use
Use on React Router archive/calendar route modules that list articles by date. Do not render inside individual article bodies.

## Structure
```tsx
<section>
    <h2 />
    <div>
        <div>{/* previous month, current month/year, next month */}</div>
        <div role="grid">{/* day headers + day buttons */}</div>
    </div>
    <div>{/* article cards */}</div>
    <nav aria-label="Article archive pagination">{/* React Router Links */}</nav>
</section>
```

## Styling Guidelines
Use Tailwind utilities: 7-column calendar grid, highlighted article days, prominent selected day, subtle today ring, clear prev/next buttons, responsive article grid/list, and standard pagination links. Use default Tailwind tokens unless the app defines shared design tokens.

## Accessibility
Calendar grid uses `role="grid"`. Day buttons are focusable, include `aria-selected`, and expose article count in `aria-label`. Month navigation buttons have descriptive labels. Pagination uses `<nav aria-label="Article archive pagination">`.

## Complete React Router Route Example

